Crewe Alexandra beat Cheltenham Town
2-0 in a playoff to return to League One, the third tier of
English soccer, after an absence of three seasons.  Nick Powell and Byron Moore, who are both products of
Creweâ€™s youth team, scored for the Railwaymen in the final at
Wembley Stadium in London today.  Crewe, unbeaten since February, finished one spot behind
Cheltenham in the regular season standings. It joins Swindon,
Shrewsbury and Crawley in achieving promotion from League Two.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
